cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on sentence-level representations using recurrent neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new model architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of max pooling layers, which are commonly used in computer vision, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model on various tasks, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
